23/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- On Monday (22 September), Minister of Public Order Luan Rama met with the head of the OSCE mission in Tirana, Osmo Lipponen, and with the head of the Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights mission, Robert Beri.
Rama briefed the officials on measures to ensure the smooth conduct of next month's local elections.
He also stressed the need to fully implement changes in the state police law, adding that he has invited opposition leader Sali Berisha to review the changes.
(ATA, BBC - 22/09/03)
